{"id": 5715, "title": "Ticket #5715: Bad cron job params object can crash schedd", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe schedd cron code creates a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CronJobParams\" title=\"Cron Job Params\">CronJobParams</a></span> object, then attempts to use it as a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAdCronJobParams\" title=\"Class Ad Cron Job Params\">ClassAdCronJobParams</a></span> object (a child class). This causes invalid memory accesses that can crash the schedd.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2016-Jun-27 15:00:24 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>Approved.  (NB: The \"extra\" function (and its declaration) are necessary for type safety, but since the parent class method being overridden was already virtual, no change was necessary there.)</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jul-05 14:51</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/6de201f8ac8eb8fdde4687cd1d513ff14a81c44b\">[48731]</a></span>: See <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5715\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5715'); return false;\" title=\"Bad cron job params object can crash schedd\">#5715</a></span>; add virtual declarations in case we need them later.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-27 15:58</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ab19c58da4885706a4f4b15e286ceaad487c35d8\">[48668]</a></span>: Version history for schedd cron crash fix. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5715\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5715'); return false;\" title=\"Bad cron job params object can crash schedd\">#5715</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-08 10:18</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ed464e3394744ed2dda2bea89827fca1123d49c3\">[48515]</a></span>: Bad cron job params object can crash schedd <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5715\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5715'); return false;\" title=\"Bad cron job params object can crash schedd\">#5715</a></span> <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ScheddCronJobMgr\" title=\"Schedd Cron Job Mgr\">ScheddCronJobMgr</a></span> needs to override CreateJobParams() to create a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAdCronJobParams\" title=\"Class Ad Cron Job Params\">ClassAdCronJobParams</a></span> object. Otherwise, a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CronJobParams\" title=\"Cron Job Params\">CronJobParams</a></span> object is created, then erroneously cast to a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAdCronJobParams\" title=\"Class Ad Cron Job Params\">ClassAdCronJobParams</a></span> object.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2016-Jun-27 15:59", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Jun-08 10:11", "fixed_version": "2016-Jun-08 10:11", "broken_version": "v080400", "priority": "2", "subsystem": "DaemonsSubmitNode", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "osg", "visibility": "public", "notify": "blin@cs.wisc.edu", "due_date": ""}